body:
We want to reserve `Analytics::sendException` for unexpected exceptions rather than for tracking how often different types of caught exceptions occur.

This may be a clumsy usage of the event fields, since I'm combining a label and the exception title into the event action. There is an `eventLabel` field that we don't seem to be using in analytics, but I'm not sure what the abbreviation for this field is - perhaps it would be better to make the event action a description of where the exception comes from (e.g. "embedded-browser-setup") and make the label store the exception title/details.

comment_data.body:
Here - and for the other jxbrowser related ones - you might instead send an event like:

`sendEvent(JxBrowserManager.ANALYTICS_CATEGORY, "setup:" + ex.getClass().getName());`

LOG.error() will also send an analytics crash event (logging at the error level). I think we can just remove the separate call to `FlutterInitializer.getAnalytics().sendException()`. I'm not sure whether this exception - from `logExceptionAndComplete()` - is user facing or not, or something we should just recover from (like a missing file) or something that indicates that we have a logic error in our code.

I assume we can either switch this to LOG.error() - and not send the exception separately - or keep it at LOG.info() and not send the exception.

It's a fairly big hammer to just catch `Exception`. Are there a few types that a thrown? If so, we should specialize what we do here based on the type of exception.

I wanted to mark all of these as `caught-exception`s, but would that perhaps be better as a label? e.g. eventCategory: `JxBrowserManager.ANALYTICS_CATEGORY`, eventAction: `setup:<Some Exception class>`, eventLabel: `caught-exception` ?

Oops, I fixed most of these `LOG.error` instances in a previous PR but missed this one. These are different errors that can occur during DevTools startup and would result in a more general user-facing message that DevTools failed to start, but I wanted the error details logged to a user's private file in case someone files a bug for any of the particular failure reasons.

It looks like there are at least two - `ExecutionException` and `TimeoutException` - but I also made this broad since missing an exception type would result in blocking running an app, and we don't need different user experiences based on the exception type.

`sendCaughtException()` ==> `sendExpectedException`?

We also might want to accept the location and exception as method params so we can combine the uniformly. Something like `(String location, Exception ex)`, and, `sendEvent("expected-exception", location + ":" + ex.getClass().getName());`.

If we think there will be expected exceptions in more than just the jxbrowser than having an event category for expected exceptions makes sense. The location / message might then be something like `jsbrowser-setup`?
OK, as long we you think we should handle the exception classes uniformly.

commit.message: Use LOG.info to prevent exception logging
Update method name and pass location and exception
